caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 51.

Exochomoscirtes buechei

sp. nov.
, male. 
A)
sternite 8; 
B)
sternite 9; 
C)
tergite 8; 
D)
tergite 9; 
E)
tegmen; 
F)
penis. Scale bar = 0.5 mm.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Sternite 8 (L 0.29, 
W 0.62
) reduced, widely U-shaped; sternite 9 (L 0.50, 
W 0.49
) consisting of paired subtriangular plates with a few apical setae, deeply emarginated on apical margin. Tergite 8 (L 0.96, 
W 0.55
) moderately sclerotized, trapezoidal, with arcuate margin, bearing row of short setae on apical margin, with a pair of long apodemes diverging basally; tergite 9 (L 0.83, 
W 0.45
) lightly sclerotized, apical portion small, with minute setae at apex, with a pair of long apodemes diverging basally. Tegmen (L 0.87, 
W 0.48
) well sclerotized, parameres wide, sinuate, inwardly hooked at apices, apices pointed, two mesal processes present, shorter one is relatively wide, longer one is very narrow and distinctly shorter than parameres. Penis (L 0.62, 
W 0.10
) well sclerotized, pala narrow and elongate, apical process evenly shorter than pala.
